Participants between 0-17:

## [1] 1

Percentage of participants who are at least 18 years old and did not fail the IMC:

percent((df.def %>% nrow() / df.total %>% nrow()))
## [1] "82%"

Number of participants in this analysis:

df.def%>% nrow()
## [1] 982

Number of participants in the final dataset that failed the manipulation check:

df.def %>% nrow() - df.def %>% filter(manipulation.check=="1") %>% nrow()
## [1] 376

Which is:

percent(df.def %>% filter(manipulation.check!="1") %>% nrow() / df.def %>% nrow(), accuracy = 0.01)
## [1] "38.29%"

Broken down in quartiles (+ group size and SE)

give.n <- function(x){
  return(c(y = mean(x)*1.1, label = length(x))) 
}

ggline(df.def, x = "manipulation.submit.quartile", y = "perceived.independence.reversed", color = "experimental.group", ylab = "Perceived independence", xlab = "Page submission - manipulation (quartiles)",  add = "mean_ci", ylim = c(2, 4.5), yticks.by = 0.5) +

7.3 Regression

t1 <- df.def %>% mutate(id = row_number()) %>% 
  select(experimental.group,
         id,
         credibility.EMA,
         credibility.post) %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  gather("key","value",-experimental.group,-id) %>% 
  mutate(post = key %>% Recode("'credibility.EMA'= 0;'credibility.post'=1"),
         EMA.credibility = value) 


tmod1 <- lmer(EMA.credibility ~ post + +(1|id),
                       data = t1)

tmod2 <- tmod1 %>% update(.~.+experimental.group) 


tmod3 <- tmod2 %>% update(.~. + post*experimental.group)

tab_model(tmod2,tmod3,
          show.ci = F,
          show.se = T,
          collapse.se = T,
          emph.p = F)
